 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Information geometrical structure $\left({{g}^{\left({{D}_{\alpha}}\right)}},{{\nabla}^{\left({{D}_{\alpha}}\right)}},{{\nabla}^{\left({{D}_{\alpha}}\right)\ast}}\right)$ induced from the sandwiched Rényi $\alpha $ -divergence ${{D}_{\alpha}}\left(\rho \parallel \sigma \right):=\frac{1}{\alpha \left(\alpha -1\right)}\log \,\text{Tr}\,{{\left({{\sigma}^{\frac{1-\alpha}{2\alpha}}}\rho \,{{\sigma}^{\frac{1-\alpha}{2\alpha}}}\right)}^{\alpha}}{{}^{{}}}$ on a finite quantum state space $\mathcal{S}$ is studied. It is shown that the Riemannian metric ${{g}^{\left({{D}_{\alpha}}\right)}}$ is monotone if and only if $\alpha \in \left(-\infty,-1\right]{\cup}^{}\left[\frac{1}{2},\infty \right)$ , and that the quantum statistical manifold $\left(\mathcal{S},{{g}^{\left({{D}_{\alpha}}\right)}},{{\nabla}^{\left({{D}_{\alpha}}\right)}},{{\nabla}^{\left({{D}_{\alpha}}\right)\ast}}\right)$ is dually flat if and only if $\alpha =1$ .</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
